# Fallout Journal

This is a personal digital journal in the Fallout/Vault-Tec style, built using HTML, Tailwind CSS, and JavaScript.

## Description

The project simulates a terminal interface with glitch and CRT effects, has:

- Header with text animations
- Gallery with pictures
- YouTube videos
- Audio player with mute/unmute button
- Collapse entries (journal entries) with animations and sounds
- Opening/closing menu and chat terminal with animations and sounds
- Post-apocalyptic style with green monochrome

## Technologies used

- HTML5
- Tailwind CSS (via CDN)
- Pure JavaScript (ES6+)
- CSS animations for glitch and CRT
- Embedded audio and video

## How to run

1. Copy all files (HTML, images, audio) to one folder
2. Open `index.html` in any modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge)
3. Enjoy interface and test interactivity

## Possible improvements

- Save the state of opening records in localStorage
- Dark/light theme
- Add real interactivity to chat (via WebSocket or API)
- Adaptability for mobile devices
- Optimize media loading
